text:
Mysterious China seeds received by dozens of Americans were identified by the USDA as seeds for herbs, vegetables and flowers.

Health departments in all 50 states have warned people not to plant the seeds, no matter how harmless the contents appear to be.

text:
Mets broadcaster Keith Hernandez asked on air, "What is a PB&J?"

“I know BLT,” Hernandez said to spit-takes from Gary Cohen and Ron Darling. “I’ve never heard a peanut butter and jelly sandwich described like that ... I’m getting out of touch.”

text:
A Queens woman detailed how she was attacked as she shot video of a No. 7 train assault.

“You get punched in the face that many times, you just don’t really know what’s going on around you,” the woman said. “I just couldn’t believe it was happening.”

text:
36 crew members tested positive for coronavirus on a cruise ship docked in Norway.

Passengers on voyages that departed July 17 and July 24 have been contacted. The rest of the crew of 158 tested negative.

name: NYDailyNews
text:
Chicago homicides are up dramatically from the 2019 total.

From Jan. 1 through July 31, there were 440 homicides in the city with a total of 2,240 people shot. There were 150 less deaths and 760 fewer shootings in Chicago during the same 2019 timeframe.
